title: Kubernetes: Pod Conditions
agents: kubernetes
catalog: containerization/kubernetes
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 A Pod's status depends on an array of PodConditions through which the
 Pod has or has not yet passed. This check monitors the status of each
 condition (scheduled, initialized, containersready, ready, resizepending,
 resizeinprogress, as well as allcontainersrestarting as of Kubernetes 1.35)
 and the duration of the condition if it is in an abnormal state. This check
 does not monitor custom conditions.

 Upper levels for WARN/CRIT can be defined to determine how much time must pass
 before an alert is triggered when a condition is in an abnormal state for an
 extended period of time.

discovery:
 One service is created representing pod conditions.
